ee trial.    Peacock offers both live and on-demand content, including sports like WWE, Golf, and Olympics, and series likeThe OfficeandYellowstone. Subscriptions start at $7.99 a month.  If you do not have cable but want to watch the Spanish-language broadcast of France vs. Argentina on Telemundo, grab afree trial to DirecTV Stream. The cable streaming service includes Telemundo in its extensive offerings, as well as other Olympics channels like NBC and USA Network.    DirecTV Stream is one of the most comprehensive live TV streaming services with up to 160+ channels, including local channels, regional sports networks, and all popular national channels. Packages start at $79.99 a month and all subscriptions start with a five-day free trial.  Another way to watch France vs. Argentina online in English is to get aVPN(virtual private network) and access the UK's Discovery+ platform. Discovery+ (UK version) is offering streams of every Olympics event, and it's cheaper than Peacock at \\u00a33.99 (a little over $5) a month. If you do not have a VPN to watch France vs. Argentina on Discovery+, we suggestExpressVPN.    ExpressVPN offers internet access in up to 160 locations around the world, making it easy to tune into local networks to watch live sports coverage online. Plans start at $12.95 a month (but right now you can get three months free when signing up for an annual package). Plus: All your info will be kept secure and private.  The France vs. Argentina Olympics soccer game is happening on Friday, Aug. 2. The match starts at 3 p.m. ET/noon PT.  We want to hear it. Send us a tip using our anonymous form.  Rolling Stone is a part of Penske Media Corporation. \\u00a9 2026 Rolling Stone, LLC. All rights reserved.\"}"